5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to abuse and exploitation of an elder; to
10 amend Section 43-8-253, Code of Alabama 1975; to provide for
11 the effect of the abuse or exploitation of an elder on
12 intestate succession, wills, joint assets, and certain other
13 contractual obligations; and to further provide for liability
14 relating to certain claims.
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
16 Section 1. Section 43-8-253, Code of Alabama 1975, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 "§43-8-253
19 (a) A surviving spouse, heir, or devisee who abuses or
20 feloniously and intentionally kills the decedent is not
21 entitled to may not receive any benefits under the will or
22 under articles 3 through 10 of this chapter, and the estate of
23 decedent passes as if the killer or abuser had predeceased the
24 decedent. Property appointed by the will of the decedent to or
25 for the benefit of the killer or abuser passes as if the
26 killer or abuser had predeceased the decedent.
27 (b) Any joint tenant who abuses or feloniously and
28 intentionally kills another joint tenant thereby effects a
